    <!-- PROCESS SECTION (RESIDENTIAL-ORIENTED) -->
    <section class="process-steps">
      <div class="section-label">Our Process</div>
      <h2>How Our {{SURFACE}} Restoration Process Works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Assess &amp; Plan</strong> — We review the condition of your {{SURFACE}}, identify issues (fading, peeling, cupping, rot), and recommend the right scope of work.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Prep &amp; Clean</strong> — Proper cleaning, stripping, and surface preparation to ensure finishes bond correctly and wear evenly.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Repair Where Needed</strong> — We address damaged boards, fasteners, or trim to restore structural integrity where applicable.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Refinish &amp; Protect</strong> — Application of appropriate stains, oils, or coatings chosen for your wood species and exposure.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Final Review</strong> — Walkthrough and final touch-ups so you are confident in both appearance and protection.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

